contentrichtext.text: {{Infobox mountain | name = Baluran | photo = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 1247 | elevation_ref = <ref name=gvp>{{cite gvp|vnum=0603-351|title=Baluran|accessdate=2011-07-03}}</ref> | prominence_m = | prominence_ref= | listing = [[Ribu]] | location = [[Java]], {{flag|Indonesia}} | range = | map = Indonesia Java | region = ID | map_caption = Location on Java | map_size = 275 | label_position = left | lat_d = 7 | lat_m = 51 | lat_s = | lat_NS = S | long_d= 114 | long_m= 22 | long_s= | long_EW= E | coordinates_ref = <ref name=gvp/> | topo = | type = [[Stratovolcano]] | age = | last_eruption = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }} '''Baluran''' is a [[stratovolcano]] located on the island of [[Java (island)|Java]]. It is at the very north east tip of the island and is overshadowed by its much large neighbour [[Ijen]]. The mountain has not erupted in historical times, although it is considered to be of [[Holocene]] age.<ref name=gvp/> ==See also== * [[List of volcanoes in Indonesia]] ==References== {{reflist}} *{{cite book | last =Witton | first =Patrick | authorlink = | coauthors = | title =Indonesia | publisher =Lonely Planet | year =2003 | location =Melbourne | pages =299 | isbn = 1-74059-154-2 }} ==External links== {{Wikivoyage-inline|Baluran National Park}} [[Category:Mountains of Indonesia]] [[Category:Stratovolcanoes]] [[Category:Subduction volcanoes]] [[Category:Volcanoes of Java]] [[Category:East Java]] {{EJava-geo-stub}}
